      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taping the edges together with a bandage is not the same as surgical closure, and a thick layer of honey will not provide the structural support needed for a deep cut. You need to manage the ooze by keeping the area clean and applying gentle pressure, not by creating a tight, potentially occlusive wrap. If the edges are gaping, they need proper alignment, which only a medical professional can ensure to prevent a long-term infection or poor healing.",
      "source": "target",
